Here is a poem about deep sleep, every line starting with the letter G, having the last word "tentacles":

Gently darkness creeps in slow 
Gliding softly to my soul 
Gathering all my worries tight 
Gripping them with an endless night 
Giving me a peaceful shore 
Glowing moonbeams light once more 
Guiding me through dreamless space 
Gathering strength in quiet place 
Growing still and calm as stone 
Gliding deep into a sleep alone 
Grasping nothing but the air 
Gently entwined by slumber's tentaclesassistant

Here is a poem about deep sleep, every line starting with the letter G, have the last word be tentacles:

Gently darkness falls around me tight 
Gliding softly into slumber's night 
Gathering strength for another day 
Giving in to exhaustion's sway 
Groggy eyes refuse to open wide 
Gently rocking back and forth inside 
Ghostly whispers echo through my mind 
Gathering secrets I've left behind 
Golden light begins to slowly fade 
Gifting me oblivion's gentle shade 
Gently wrapping me in silent sleep 
Giving myself over to dreamless deep 
Going under where the shadows creep 
Grabbing hold of nothing but the dark tentaclesassistant
